271
00:10:37,328 --> 00:10:39,188
We took the underground to aldersgate and

272
00:10:39,788 --> 00:10:42,828
walked to saxe, coburg square. It was a

273
00:10:42,948 --> 00:10:45,468
small, poor, quiet square.

274
00:10:45,628 --> 00:10:47,828
Wilson's pawn shop had three gold balls

275
00:10:48,088 --> 00:10:50,868
outside, the sign of a pawn shop.

276
00:10:51,028 --> 00:10:53,248
Holmes looked at the shop and walked up

277
00:10:53,508 --> 00:10:55,708
and down the street. Then he knocked on

278
00:10:55,948 --> 00:10:56,588
the door.

279
00:10:56,748 --> 00:10:59,508
A young clean, shaven man opened it.

280
00:10:59,668 --> 00:11:02,028
Holmes asked, how do i go to the strand?

281
00:11:02,188 --> 00:11:04,648
Third right, fourth left, the man said

282
00:11:04,988 --> 00:11:07,028
quickly, and closed the door.

283
00:11:07,188 --> 00:11:10,308
A smart man! Holmes said. Maybe the fourth

284
00:11:10,428 --> 00:11:11,528
smartest man in london.

285
00:11:11,688 --> 00:11:13,348
You wanted to see the assistant, not the

286
00:11:13,528 --> 00:11:14,848
way, i said.

287
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:18,768
No. I wanted to see his trousers knees.

288
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:20,008
Why did you hit the pavement with your

289
00:11:20,128 --> 00:11:20,828
stick?

290
00:11:20,988 --> 00:11:24,268
Now we observe, watson. We are like spies.

291
00:11:24,428 --> 00:11:26,208
We walked around the corner to a big busy

292
00:11:26,448 --> 00:11:28,168
street with many shops.

293
00:11:28,328 --> 00:11:30,548
Holmes named the buildings, a tobacconist,

294
00:11:30,988 --> 00:11:34,048
a bank, a restaurant, a carriage shop.

295
00:11:45,501 --> 00:11:48,121
Now, doctor, work is finished. Let us eat

296
00:11:48,421 --> 00:11:50,121
and go to the concert.

297
00:11:50,281 --> 00:11:51,881
In the afternoon holmes listened to music

298
00:11:51,981 --> 00:11:53,441
and was very happy.

299
00:11:53,601 --> 00:11:55,901
His face looked dreamy, not like the sharp

300
00:11:56,081 --> 00:11:57,621
detective i knew.

301
00:11:57,781 --> 00:11:59,681
But i felt danger was coming for the

302
00:11:59,761 --> 00:12:00,921
criminals he hunted.

303
00:12:01,081 --> 00:12:02,501
When we left, holmes said, go home,

304
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:06,101
watson. I have work. This case is serious.

305
00:12:06,261 --> 00:12:08,281
A crime is planned. We can stop it. I need

306
00:12:08,461 --> 00:12:11,521
you tonight at ten. Bring your gun.

307
00:12:11,681 --> 00:12:13,381
He left in the crowd. I did not understand

308
00:12:14,021 --> 00:12:15,061
what he knew.

309
00:12:15,221 --> 00:12:16,821
I thought about the red, headed league,

310
00:12:17,061 --> 00:12:18,581
the shop, and the bank.

311
00:12:18,741 --> 00:12:21,081
At a quarter past nine i came to baker

312
00:12:21,221 --> 00:12:24,481
street. Two cabs waited outside.

313
00:12:24,641 --> 00:12:26,881
Holmes talked with two men, peter jones

314
00:12:26,921 --> 00:12:29,341
from scotland yard, and mr.

315
00:12:29,501 --> 00:12:31,861
Merryweather from the bank, a thin sad man

316
00:12:32,181 --> 00:12:33,521
in a black coat.

317
00:12:33,681 --> 00:12:36,921
Our group is ready, holmes said. Watson,

318
00:12:37,601 --> 00:12:40,581
this is jones. This is merryweather.

319
00:12:40,741 --> 00:12:42,821
Tonight's game is bigger than cards.

320
00:12:42,981 --> 00:12:44,541
For you, mr. Merryweather, thirty thousand

321
00:12:44,821 --> 00:12:47,061
pounds are at risk, holmes said.

322
00:12:47,221 --> 00:12:50,881
For you, jones, the man is john clay, a

323
00:12:50,921 --> 00:12:52,701
thief and forger, one of the best

324
00:12:52,821 --> 00:12:54,801
criminals in london.

325
00:12:54,961 --> 00:12:57,181
I hope we do not chase a wild goose,

326
00:12:57,701 --> 00:12:58,801
merryweather said.

327
00:12:58,961 --> 00:13:01,441
Trust holmes, jones said.

328
00:13:01,681 --> 00:13:05,101
It is after ten. Let us go, holmes said.

329
00:13:05,261 --> 00:13:07,921
Holmes was quiet in the cab. We drove

330
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:11,121
through london to farringdon street.

331
00:13:11,281 --> 00:13:13,981
We are near, holmes said. Merryweather is

332
00:13:14,201 --> 00:13:16,861
a bank director. Jones is brave and will

333
00:13:16,981 --> 00:13:17,901
not let go.

334
00:13:18,061 --> 00:13:19,461
We walked through a narrow passage and

335
00:13:20,101 --> 00:13:22,641
down stone steps behind iron doors.

336
00:13:23,661 --> 00:13:25,701
Merryweather lit a lantern.

337
00:13:25,861 --> 00:13:27,741
We entered a large dark cellar full of

338
00:13:27,841 --> 00:13:28,861
boxes.

339
00:13:29,021 --> 00:13:31,481
Holmes looked around. Not easy to attack

340
00:13:31,721 --> 00:13:32,641
from above.

341
00:13:32,801 --> 00:13:34,421
Merryweather hit the floor with his stick.

342
00:13:35,321 --> 00:13:36,601
The floor sounded hollow.

343
00:13:36,761 --> 00:13:39,121
Please be quiet, holmes said. You can

344
00:13:39,241 --> 00:13:42,201
break our plan. Sit on those boxes.

345
00:13:42,361 --> 00:13:44,121
Holmes knelt and looked at the floor with

346
00:13:44,381 --> 00:13:47,081
a magnifying glass. Then he stood up.

347
00:13:47,321 --> 00:13:48,861
We have about one hour, he said. We are in

348
00:13:48,901 --> 00:13:50,761
the cellar of a big london bank.

349
00:13:50,921 --> 00:13:53,061
The bank keeps french gold here, thirty

350
00:13:53,101 --> 00:13:56,221
thousand gold coins. Criminals want this

351
00:13:56,481 --> 00:13:57,241
gold.

352
00:13:57,401 --> 00:13:58,801
We must turn off the light and wait,

353
00:13:59,341 --> 00:14:02,241
holmes said. Hide behind the boxes.

354
00:14:04,601 --> 00:14:08,721
When i shine my light, run fast. Watson,

355
00:14:09,401 --> 00:14:11,661
if they shoot, you can shoot too.

356
00:14:11,821 --> 00:14:13,901
I put my gun ready. Holmes turned off the

357
00:14:14,081 --> 00:14:16,401
lantern. It was completely dark and cold.

358
00:14:16,561 --> 00:14:18,001
We waited in silence.

359
00:14:31,053 --> 00:14:33,133
Holmes whispered, they can only go back to

360
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:35,653
wilson's shop. Jones, are men at the front

361
00:14:35,773 --> 00:14:36,253
door?

362
00:14:36,413 --> 00:14:39,153
Yes. An inspector and two policemen.

363
00:14:39,313 --> 00:14:41,133
Good. Now we wait.

364
00:14:41,293 --> 00:14:43,393
It felt like all night, but it was only

365
00:14:43,513 --> 00:14:45,253
about one hour.

366
00:14:45,413 --> 00:14:47,933
I was tired and afraid to move. I heard my

367
00:14:48,093 --> 00:14:49,113
friends breathing.

368
00:14:49,273 --> 00:14:52,773
Then i saw a small light on the floor. It

369
00:14:52,793 --> 00:14:54,273
became a yellow line.

370
00:14:54,433 --> 00:14:55,873
A hand came up through the stones and

371
00:14:56,353 --> 00:14:59,133
moved in the light. Then the hand went

372
00:14:59,373 --> 00:14:59,813
away.

373
00:14:59,973 --> 00:15:01,693
Everything was dark again.

374
00:15:05,031 --> 00:15:06,971
For a minute a hand came up through the

375
00:15:07,111 --> 00:15:10,831
floor, then went back. A stone moved.

376
00:15:10,991 --> 00:15:13,411
A hole opened. Light came up. A young man

377
00:15:13,651 --> 00:15:16,111
climbed out. A small man with red hair

378
00:15:16,311 --> 00:15:16,971
followed.

379
00:15:17,131 --> 00:15:18,351
It's clear, he whispered. Do you have the

380
00:15:18,491 --> 00:15:19,251
bags?

381
00:15:19,411 --> 00:15:21,271
Holmes caught the first man. The second

382
00:15:21,451 --> 00:15:23,831
man tried to escape down the hole. Jones

383
00:15:23,911 --> 00:15:24,951
caught his coat.

384
00:15:25,111 --> 00:15:27,771
A gun fell when holmes hit the man's arm.

385
00:15:27,931 --> 00:15:30,231
It's no use, john clay, holmes said.

386
00:15:30,391 --> 00:15:33,611
Clay smiled. You did well. Your red,

387
00:15:33,931 --> 00:15:35,591
headed league trick was clever.

388
00:15:35,751 --> 00:15:38,051
Police took clay away. Merryweather

389
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:40,711
thanked holmes for saving the bank gold.

390
00:15:40,871 --> 00:15:42,551
Later at baker street holmes told me

391
00:15:42,771 --> 00:15:45,111
again, the league was only a trick to keep

392
00:15:45,231 --> 00:15:46,431
wilson away.

393
00:15:46,591 --> 00:15:49,211
Clay dug from the cellar to the bank. When

394
00:15:49,271 --> 00:15:51,631
the office closed, the tunnel was ready.

395
00:15:51,831 --> 00:15:54,631
They chose saturday night to steal and

396
00:15:55,331 --> 00:15:57,231
escape on sunday.

397
00:15:57,391 --> 00:15:59,651
You see every step, i said.

398
00:15:59,811 --> 00:16:01,471
Yes, holmes said. Now i need a little

399
00:16:01,571 --> 00:16:03,991
rest, and maybe another strange case soon.
